<paragraph blockId="33.[826,1441,659,773]" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis box="[826,952,659,680]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">Etymology:</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[1004,1061,690,711]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">brevi</emphasis>
meaning short and 
<emphasis box="[1356,1441,691,712]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="532">pinguis</emphasis>
meaning stout, referring to the unique shape of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
